HTML/HTML5 Notes:

<!DOCTYPE html)> ---mandatory at the top of all docs.
<html> wraps around entirety of your page's content and code
</html>

<head> element for metadata elements (link,  meta, title, style)
</head>

<!--
comment out code
-->

<body> element for displayed content for users</body>

<h(1-6)>Header Element goes here</h(1-6)>
(

<p>This is a paragraph element (Text strings basically)</p>

<main> Wraps around primary content of page </main>(paragraphs, images, not headers and footers?)

<div>division element, a general purpose container for other elements.(it is very commonly used, they say)</div>

<img src="http://urltomyimage.com" alt="Text describing image(if it doesn't load">

Anchor Elements - Link to other webpages or to content on your own site
target="_blank" opens link in new tab
href="#" -dead link
Can also nest around elements like images

<a href="http://urltodestination.com/" target="_blank">Text of link</a> (external)

<a href="destination-url">Text of link</a>
...
<element id="destination id">Element Text</element>

unordered lists (multiple lines with bullet points)
<ul>
    <li>item 1</li>
    <li>item 2</li>
    <li>item 3</li>
</ul>

ordered/numbered lists nest in <ol></ol>

<input type="text" placeholder="enter placeholder text here"> 
input element for users to enter text
input types:
    "text"
    "radio"
    "checkbox"
additional input attributes:
    required- makes completion mandatory prior to submission
	checked - makes specific input selected at start

form element
<form action="/url-for-form-submission-destination">
form content (<inputs><buttons>)
</form>

<button type="submit"(or other types)>Text for your button goes here</button>

Example of a form with various inputs:
<form action="/submit-cat-photo">
    <label for="indoor"><input id="indoor" type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor"> Indoor</label>
    <label for="outdoor"><input id="outdoor" type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor"> Outdoor</label><br>
    <label for="indignant"><input id="indignant" type="checkbox" name="personality">Indignant</label>
    <label for="snooty"><input id="snooty" type="checkbox" name="personality">Snooty</label>
    <label for="conniving"><input id="conniving" type ="checkbox" name="personality">Conniving</label><br>
    <input type="text" placeholder="cat photo URL" required>
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

<br> - break point (newline, basically?)
